Preheat your #oven to 220°C. Put a large #saucepan of water with a pinch of @salt{pinch} on to boil for the potatoes. Chop the @red potato{1} into roughly 2cm chunks (no need to peel!). Put the potato into the #pot of boiling water and cook for ~{15-20%minutes}.

> The potato is cooked when you can easily slip a knife through.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander then pop back into the #pot with the lid on.

Remove the root and dark green top from the @leek{1}, halve lengthways and slice into 1cm thick half moons. Twist and tear the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} in half. Pick the parsley leaves from their stalks and roughly chop. Finely chop the stalks (keep them separate). Drain and rinse the @sweetcorn{1/2%cup} in a colander or #sieve. Chop the @smoked fish mix{215%g} into 2cm chunks, leaving the prawns whole.

Put a #frying pan or wide bottomed #saucepan on medium heat with a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} and add the leek, along with a pinch of @salt{} and a grind of @black pepper{grind}. Cook until soft, stirring frequently, ~{6-7%minutes}. Once soft, add the sweetcorn and parsley stalks and stir together. Cook for a further ~{2%minutes}, stirring gently.

Add the @water{25%ml} and @fish stock powder{1%tsp} to the leek and sweetcorn. Stir to dissolve the stock powder. Add the @creme fraiche{1%tbsp}, stir together and bring to the boil, then taste the sauce. Add more salt and black pepper if necessary. Put the fish mix in the bottom of an #ovenproof dish and spoon your veggies and all the sauce on top, gently stir to combine.

When the potatoes are drained and back in the #pot, add the parsley leaves, @butter{rate} and a splash of @?milk{splash} (if you have some). Mash with a #potato masher{} until smooth, taste and add more salt and black pepper to your liking. Spoon the mashed potato on top of the fish and veggies and flatten it out with your spoon. Use a fork to make lines in the top of the pie.

> Brush with a little oil if you want a super crispy finish.

Bake the fish pie on the top shelf of your #oven until the potato is crispy and the fish is cooked, ~{20%minutes}.

> The fish is cooked when the centre is opaque.

While the pie is cooking, do the washing up! When ready, spoon the fish pie into #bowls and devour. Enjoy!